Travelling abroad is something that is associated with a lot of joy and excitement. Visiting foreign lands
column15: sampling exotic cuisine and experiencing a vivid and contrasting culture but there are so many things that we don\u2019t consider. We look at air travel through rose-tinted glasses
column16: oblivious to the tedious and troublesome nitty gritties it involves. It\u2019s not the same as travelling within the domestic territory as there are far more formalities and the laws are stringent and subjective depending on the country you are travelling to. Passport
column18: visa and customs make things a little difficult for you. Clear all the documents
column19:
take a deep breath and walk into the airport with your Kara Backpack and everything will be alright.

\r\n

\r\n\tYou stroll through the airport
column21: check in and baggage checks are a breeze. You are sipping coffee and reading a book while you wait for the flight. This unisex strolley bag makes things easy as you don\u2019t have to carry around this load. You can freely move about the length and breadth of the airport without feeling bogged down. It\u2019s time to board the flight and you are greeted by the pretty air-hostess. This backpack measures 355.6 x 431.8 x 152.4 mm in dimension and can be comfortably stored in the overhead compartment. It is ideal for such travel as it is made of nylon which is a durable fabric that can be easily cleaned. You take your seat and wait for a drink

your first flight seems to be a success.
